<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="nomenclature">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,503,908,934]" box="[151,503,908,934]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<heading bold="true" box="[151,503,908,934]" fontSize="11" level="1" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" reason="1">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,503,908,934]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[151,251,908,934]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Ferdina</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[257,503,908,934]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
in the 
<taxonomicName box="[334,503,908,934]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,978,1579]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Observations of 
<taxonomicName box="[342,431,979,1003]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[342,431,979,1003]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
specimens identify several characters that support placement within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1274,1433,978,1003]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
. These include the presence of goniasterid-like abactinal plates arranged into a flattened surface framed by a distinct marginal plate arrangement in juveniles of 
<taxonomicName box="[660,822,1051,1075]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="mena" status="n. sp.">
<emphasis box="[660,822,1051,1075]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina mena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis bold="true" box="[834,901,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[834,901,1050,1075]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">n. sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
(
<figureCitation box="[921,995,1050,1075]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1395,1417]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,199,1337]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,163,1374]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ferdina mena n. sp. Small goniasterid-like specimens. MNHN-IE- 2007 - 4941. Scale Bar = 1.5 mm A. Abactinal surface. B. A bactinal surface detail. C. Lateral view showing paired bare regions in each interradius. D. Actinal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/583198/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Fig. 6</figureCitation>
). As outlined in the introduction, the placement of 
<taxonomicName box="[306,395,1086,1110]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[306,395,1086,1110]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
in the 
<taxonomicName box="[476,632,1086,1111]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
was first considered by 
<bibRefCitation author="Viguier" box="[911,1071,1086,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Viguier, C. (1878) Classification des Stellerides. Comptes Rendus de l'Academie des Sciences de Paris, 84, 681 - 583. [also in Annals of the Magazine of Natural History, 2 (5), 103 - 105]" type="journal article" year="1878">Viguier (1878</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Viguier" box="[1084,1141,1087,1111]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Viguier, C. (1879) Anatomie comparee du squelette des Stellerides. Archives de Zoologie Experimentale et Generale, 7, 33 - 250." type="journal article" year="1879">1879</bibRefCitation>
) with some agreement by 
<bibRefCitation author="Fisher" box="[151,310,1122,1147]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Fisher, W. K. (1919) Starfishes of the Philippine seas and adjacent waters. Bulletin of the United States National Museum, 3 (100), 1 - 547, 156 pls." type="journal article" year="1919">Fisher (1919)</bibRefCitation>
. The placement of 
<taxonomicName box="[543,668,1123,1147]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Neoferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[543,668,1123,1147]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Neoferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
within the 
<taxonomicName box="[809,965,1122,1147]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
by 
<bibRefCitation author="Mah" box="[1016,1274,1122,1147]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Mah, C. L. &amp; Foltz, D. W. (2011) Molecular Phylogeny of the Valvatacea (Asteroidea, Echinodermata). Zoological Journal of the Linnean Society, 161, 769 - 788." type="journal article" year="2011">Mah and Foltz (2011)</bibRefCitation>
supported by molecular data, suggests that a closely related genus with shared characters (e.g., furrow spination, granulate tegument covering adambulacrals) such as 
<taxonomicName box="[633,722,1195,1219]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[633,722,1195,1219]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
can also be plausibly classified within the 
<taxonomicName box="[1201,1360,1194,1219]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
. 
<bibRefCitation author="Blake" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" refString="Blake, D. B. &amp; Reid, R. (1998) Some Albian (Cretaceous) Asteroids (Echinodermata) from Texas and their paleobiological implications. Journal of Paleontology, 72 (3), 512 - 532." type="journal article" year="1998">Blake and Reid (1998)</bibRefCitation>
also noted goniasterid affinities when comparing members of the “ 
<taxonomicName box="[1134,1224,1230,1254]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1134,1224,1230,1254]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
group”, including 
<emphasis box="[151,522,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
<taxonomicName box="[151,243,1267,1291]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Ferdina</taxonomicName>
, 
<taxonomicName box="[254,390,1267,1291]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Paraferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Paraferdina</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicName box="[397,522,1267,1291]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" genus="Neoferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">Neoferdina</taxonomicName>
</emphasis>
and 
<taxonomicName box="[576,706,1267,1291]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Sinoferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[576,706,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Sinoferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
with the Cretaceous 
<taxonomicName box="[942,1037,1267,1291]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Denebia" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[942,1037,1267,1291]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Denebia</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="17" pageNumber="18" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="17.[151,1437,978,1579]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">
Relatively small individuals of 
<taxonomicName box="[562,721,1302,1326]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="mena" status="n.sp.">
<emphasis box="[562,721,1302,1326]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina mena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel box="[731,784,1303,1326]" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" rank="species">n.sp.</taxonomicNameLabel>
(e.g. MNHN-IE-2007-4941 at R= 
<quantity box="[1189,1270,1303,1327]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.2" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" unit="cm" value="1.2">1.2 cm</quantity>
) show a welldeveloped marginal series with a more quadrate and blocky morphology forming a distinct frame around the abactinal plates (
<figureCitation box="[343,423,1374,1399]" captionStart="FIGURE 6" captionStartId="21.[151,250,1395,1417]" captionTargetBox="[200,1384,199,1337]" captionTargetId="figure@21.[151,1436,163,1374]" captionTargetPageId="21" captionText="FIGURE 6. Ferdina mena n. sp. Small goniasterid-like specimens. MNHN-IE- 2007 - 4941. Scale Bar = 1.5 mm A. Abactinal surface. B. A bactinal surface detail. C. Lateral view showing paired bare regions in each interradius. D. Actinal surface." httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/583198/files/figure.png" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Figs. 6</figureCitation>
A–C). Although the marginal plate morphology and arrangement appear to vary more in larger individuals, these smaller specimens suggest synapomorphies for placement in the 
<taxonomicName box="[1196,1355,1410,1435]" class="Asteroidea" family="Goniasteridae" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="family">Goniasteridae</taxonomicName>
. These specimens also show the arm as quadrate in cross-section as opposed to larger individuals with a more rounded or convex abactinal surface. Although juveniles of the other two 
<taxonomicName box="[876,965,1483,1507]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[876,965,1483,1507]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">Ferdina</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
spp. were unavailable, those of 
<taxonomicName box="[1345,1432,1483,1506]" class="Asteroidea" family="Ophidiasteridae" genus="Ferdina" kingdom="Animalia" order="Valvatida" pageId="17" pageNumber="18" phylum="Echinodermata" rank="species" species="mena">
<emphasis box="[1345,1432,1483,1506]" italics="true" pageId="17" pageNumber="18">F. mena</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
would suggest that there is a transformation in the shape/convexity of the abactinal surface and arm shape as this species increases in size.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
